# Research Workflow

Rules for integrating knowledge synthesis into the daily and weekly research process.

## Research Phases

Each phase maps to specific knowledge actions:

| Phase | Knowledge Action | System Feature |
|-------|-----------------|---------------|
| Question Formation | Search for prior thinking on the topic | Semantic search, graph browse |
| Literature Review | Ingest and classify new sources | Ingestion pipeline |
| Reading | Create literature notes, apply progressive summarization | Note creation, highlighting |
| Analysis | Create permanent notes, link to graph | Zettelkasten, graph construction |
| Synthesis | Build topic summaries, concept maps | Summarization hierarchy |
| Writing | Retrieve and cite from knowledge base | Citation manager, search |
| Revision | Update notes with new understanding | Version tracking |
| Publication | Export bibliography, archive project notes | Export, archival |

## Daily Routine (30-45 minutes)

### Morning (15 minutes)
- Process fleeting notes inbox: convert to literature/permanent notes or discard
- Review 3-5 random permanent notes via spaced repetition
- Check for new documents awaiting ingestion

### During Work
- Capture fleeting notes as ideas occur (do not interrupt deep work to process them)
- Create literature notes while actively reading
- Link new notes to existing knowledge immediately

### Evening (15 minutes)
- Process remaining fleeting notes
- Update structure notes if topic clusters shifted
- Log one "idea of the day" for future review

## Weekly Review (60-90 minutes)

### Inbox Zero
- All fleeting notes processed or discarded
- All new documents classified and metadata complete
- All highlights converted to literature notes

### Graph Maintenance
- Review orphan notes and link or archive them
- Merge duplicate concept nodes
- Update structure notes and maps of content

### Summarization
- Write or update one topic summary
- Promote mature literature notes to permanent status

### Reflection
- What surprised me this week?
- What contradicted my prior understanding?
- What question do I want to explore next week?

## Note Processing Rules

### Fleeting Notes
- Must be processed within 48 hours or explicitly archived
- Never link fleeting notes to the knowledge graph directly
- A fleeting note becomes either a literature note, a permanent note, or trash

### Literature Notes
- One note per key idea (not one note per source)
- Written in your own words, never copy-paste
- Always linked to the bibliographic record
- Tagged with source, topic, and date

### Permanent Notes
- Atomic: exactly one idea
- Self-contained: understandable without reading the source
- Connected: at least one link to another permanent note
- Versioned: includes creation date and update log

## Integration Points

| External Tool | Sync Method | Direction |
|--------------|-------------|-----------|
