| Writing Tool | Citation insertion | From system |
| Web Browser | Clip extension | Into system |

## Version Tracking

When understanding of an idea changes:

1. Create a new version of the note (do not overwrite)
2. Add a change log entry: date, what changed, what triggered the change
3. Link the new version to the previous version
4. Update all incoming links to point to the latest version
5. Mark the old version as superseded (never delete)

## Project Lifecycle

When starting a research project:

1. Search existing notes for prior thinking
2. Create a project structure note linking all relevant permanent notes
3. Identify gaps in current knowledge
4. Build a targeted reading list to fill gaps
5. Track project-specific notes separately (they are temporary)

When completing a project:

1. Promote any project notes worth keeping to permanent status
2. Archive remaining project notes
3. Update topic summaries affected by the project
4. Export bibliography for the final output
5. Write a brief retrospective: what did this project teach me?
